body:
Yosys 0.6 (git sha1 124f7c4) fails to detect the width of memory access in the following code

```
module m ();
  wire [0:0] foo[0:0];
  wire [0:0] bar[0:0];
  wire baz;

  assign foo[0] = {1{1'b0}};  // Replace with "assign foo[0] = 1'b0;" and yosys accepts the code
  assign bar[0] = 1'b0;
  assign baz = bar[foo[0]];
endmodule
```

If the assignment to foo is replace with the code in the comment, yosys manages to detect the width of the memory access. Expected behavior is that both of these variants of the above code works.

By the way, yosys 0.6 prints "Failed to detect with of memory access", that is, "with" instead of "width".

